prompt 1:
I am a new software developer and I want you to help me build a landing page of a children’s clothing company called CHILDREN SMART.

prompt 2: 
The landing page should have the following sections:
 A menu bar, logo, and a search bar all on the same level 
Let the menu be sticky and let it have the following items with a drop down in each of them:
- product 
- services
- customer service 
- contact us 

promp 3:
Let the menu bar be captured inside a blue-colored frame. Let the lettering be white so they are legible 

prompt 4:
Create a logo for me and place it at the top left hand side of the landing page 

prompt 5:
Let the search bar sit on the top right hand side of the menu bar.

prompt 6:
A panel that sits on the left hand side of the menu bar. Let users be able to navigate to the main section using the links here.

prompt 7:
This section should have the following listed links, arranged in a stack format. Each of these should be clickable. When clicked, each should lead to the relevant row in the main section of the landing page
  - Children's Shoes
  - Girls' Toys
  - Boys' Toys
  - Sample School Uniforms
  - Girls' Blouses
  - Boys' Trousers
  - Girls' Skirts 

prompt 8:
A hero section that is about 35% of the length of the landing page and 100% of its width 
Let the hero section have a purple background 

prompt 9:
Let the hero section have an image of kids clothe and a write up under the image and place them at the right hand side of the hero section.

prompt 10:
Let the hero section have a welcoming headline and a tagline, and a Shop now link under it. Place them at the left hand side of the hero section.

prompt 11:
 A main body divided into 7 rows with each row having 5 product cards filled with children’s items relevant to the
- shoes should have different types: male sandals, female sandals, laced shoes, non-laced shoes etc.
- Girls’ toys should have different types
- Boys’ toys should have different types 
- School uniforms should have different types 
- Girls’ blouses should have different types 
- Boys’ trousers should have different types 
- Girls’ skirts should have different types 

prompt 12:
A footer that has all the copyright, and social media links of the company 

prompt 13:
Build me this using HTML and CSS. Do not use inline styling for CSS.
Let the IDE be Visual Studio Code

prompt 14:
Kindly insert comments in your code so that my team members will be able to interpret and understand your code a lot faster. 

prompt 15:
My theme color is blue and pink.

prompt 16:
Use pictures with good quality and the right aspect ratio.

prompt 17:
Document everything  on the Landing Page using the Dewey classification system

1.0 = LANDING PAGE

1.1 = MENU SECTION
1.1.1 Logo Section

1.1.2 Navigation Menu
1.1.2.1 Products Dropdown
1.1.2.2 Services Dropdown
